h <i>feld</i> ‘open country’.","Irish (Waterford): when not an importation of 1, this is an altered form of the Norman name <b>de Manville</b> (see   Mandeville   3).","Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic) <b>Mansfeld</b>, a habitational name from a place so called in Saxony."]},{"name":"Manderville","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Manwell","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Manville","meanings":["English (Sussex and Lancashire): variant of   Mandeville  .","Altered form of   Mainville   1, a surname of Swiss French origin (see   Miville  ).","French: variant of <b>Menville</b>, a habitational name from Menville in Haute-Garonne, and also of   Mainville   2."]},{"name":"Mundell","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  .","Americanized form of German <b>Mündel</b> (or some other similar, like-sounding surname): nickname for someone with a prominent mouth, from Middle High German <i>munt</i>, <i>mündelīn</i> ‘(little) mouth’."]},{"name":"Monville","meanings":["Altered form of French   Mandeville  .","Walloon: habitational name from Monville in Namur province in Wallonia (Belgium), of the same etymology as in 3 below.","In some cases possibly also French: habitational name from Montville in Seine-Maritime or Monville in Calvados, both named with Old French <i>mont</i> ‘mountain, hill’ + <i>ville</i> ‘settlement’."]},{"name":"Mandal","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Chandi, Sanjay, Sankar, Somnath, Aditi, Aditya, Ajit, Amala, Amitabha, Anil, Anirudh, Aparna.","Indian (northern states): from Sanskrit <i>maṇḍala</i>, a word that has several meanings, including ‘sphere’ and ‘halo’.","English (Cumbria; of Norman origin): variant of   Mandeville  ."]},{"name":"Montville","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Vernice.","Altered form of French   Mandeville  .","French: variant of   Monville  . This surname is very rare in France, found mainly in Creuse."]},{"name":"Manfull","meanings":["English (Midlands): probably a variant of   Mandeville  . Compare   Manville  ."]}]},{"name":"Beatrice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["and French form of   Beatrix  , which was quite popular in England during the Middle Ages, and strongly revived in the 19th century. It is most famous as the name of Dante's beloved, and is borne by the elder (  b. 1988 ) of the Duke of York's daughters."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Beatrice Andeville was born about 1199, in Andeville, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, France. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Nicholas Malmains. She died about 1240, at the age of 43."},"et":{"about 1199–about 1240":"umbes 1199–umbes 1240","1204–1240":"1204–1240","1220–Female":"1220–Surnud","1228–1291":"1228–1291","1199–1240":"1199–1240","1228":"1228","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","1204":"1204","about 1228":"umbes 1228","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","about 1199":"umbes 1199","about 1240":"umbes 1240","1291":"1291","Andeville, Eure-et-Loir, France":"Andeville, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Burton, Northamptonshire, England":"Burton, Hampshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1199–about 1240":"noin 1199–noin 1240","1204–1240":"1204–1240","1220–Female":"1220–Kuollut","1228–1291":"1228–1291","1199–1240":"1199–1240","1228":"1228","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","1204":"1204","about 1228":"noin 1228","1199":"1199","1220":"1220","1240":"1240","about 1199":"noin 1199","about 1240":"noin 1240","1291":"1291","Andeville, Eure-et-Loir, France":"Andeville, Eure-et-Loir, Centre, Ranska","Burton, Northamptonshire, England":"Burton, Hampshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1199–about 1240":"environ 1199–environ 1240","1204–1240":"1204–1240","1220–Female":"1220–Décédée","1228–1291":"1228–1291","1199–1240":"1199–1240","1228":"1228","Abt 1240":"environ 1240","1204":"1204","about 1228":"environ 1228","1199":"1199","1